Australian GP: Lewis Hamilton delighted with 'awesome' weekend
World champion Lewis Hamilton reflects on an "amazing" weekend afterwinning the opening race of the 2015 season in Australia.Hamilton lead home team-mate Nico Rosberg with third placed Sebastian Vettel over 30 seconds behind the Mercedes duo in Melbourne.And ominously for the rest of the grid Hamilton says "I'll know I'm going to improve in the next race" in Malaysia.Available to UK users only.